  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF COUNTERATTACK</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Rogue</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;53</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;9 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;60 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;53 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline the rogue will automatically riposte every attack landed on them by the opponent they are facing.  This discipline lasts for 9 seconds and has a base reuse time of 60 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the rogue gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>54 RAKE</span><b>, By Poisin daggerfist</b><br><br>This is not an escape skill unless you want to run backwards.  You cannot ripost attacks from the rear.  You also do not see a ripost message, only the attack damage like a normal attack.  Nice discipline tho becasue some MOB will not evade for some reason and you end up tanking. Another use is to stop a train long enough for your chanter to mes them all.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>I'M A ROGUE AND I LIKE IT</span><b>, By Maddy</b><br><br>Hey just think if it this way.  almost every mob at about this level can dual wield and double atack for insane amounts of damage.  PoS comes to mind.  This will save you for a good 9 secs!  Damn it takes me 1 second to do 242 damage! (BS baby Yeah!)  Think what these uber mobs can do to you.  And you know how long it takes to stun and root or what ever a mob?  under 9 seconds for a good group.

<p>You just became what a rogue should be, a great distraction! =)<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>PLUS AND MINUS</span><b>, By Veran aereighnt'eihz</b><br><br>This discipline can be useful, during the 9 seconds it may give a rogue enough time to use it and zone.

<p>On the negative side, 9 seconds of this discipline with a re-use of 60 minutes is too much, even at lvl 60, when the re-use time is decreased to 53 minutes.  

<p>Chances are, when you are in kunark and you have to use this discipline, you may still die because either the enemy casts a spell which this discipline won't repel, or during the 9 seconds you couldn't make it to the zone because zones in kunark are huge.

<p>I save this discipline until I need to use it because it's re-use time is too long, and it can be used to save your life, although in some cases it won't.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>USEFULLNESS</span><b>, By Tork - nameless</b><br><br><p>You're being shortsighted.

<p>Yes, 9 seconds is a short duration, but think about the last time you did a dragon or God and he just stuck on you like white on rice.  Wouldn't it be great to kick off this while his attention was focused on you?  How about that bad pull before the enchanter can got off AE stun and you happened to be standing in the wrong place?


<p>Think of this and your other disciplines more in terms of specalized applications, i.e., his is similar to a 1/2 duration melee DA -  you don't see clerics crying that DA is useless.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>UGH.</span><b>, By Hawktel</b><br><br>I'm not a rogue, but its very easy to see how to use this.
<p>First though, you do get a clear indication of Riposte damage. This is what it will look like:
<p>You swing and hit the ghoul lord for 29 damage.
The ghoul lord swings at you but you Reposte!
<p>Now, to use this: Tell the people in the group before hand you plan to use a Discipline that requires them to leave the mob hitting you for 9 seconds. And that You will tell them when your going to use it and  for them not to Taunt. Also tell them that your going to tell them the second they can taunt, and you'd like it if they could get it off you when you ask them to. Also mention to your Cleric that your going to need a heal.
<p>Then on the next hard pull where people are worried about winning, as the puller comes in, BS the mob, and turn on the disapline. For 9 second its will frenzy on you. At the end of the 9 seconds hit evade, and have a Hotkeyed, &#34;please get it off me now&#34;

<p>Taa-daa... A useful discipline.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
